This article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on September 4, 2020, in recognition of Labor Day. The proclamation celebrates the American workforce and their contributions to the nation's economy. It acknowledges the challenges faced by workers during the global pandemic and highlights the importance of essential workers in maintaining the country's way of life. The proclamation also mentions the actions taken by the administration to support businesses and workers, such as the Paycheck Protection Program and funding for apprenticeship programs. The President expresses gratitude to workers and calls for the observance of Labor Day with appropriate programs and activities.